where formula_52,formula_53 are the inertial axes components of velocity. According to Newton&#x27;s Second Law, the accelerations are proportional to the forces, so the forces in inertial axes are:

::formula_54
::formula_55

where &quot;m&quot; is the mass.
By the nature of the motion, the speed variation formula_56 is negligible over the period of the oscillation, so:

