* Luca Signorelli â &quot;The Adoration of the Shepherds&quot; ()
* Andrea Mantegna â &quot;San Zeno Altarpiece&quot; (1459)
* Stanley Spencer â Sandham Memorial Chapel, Burghclere, Hants.
* Pre-Raphaelite Dante Rossetti revisited the predella in his second Beata Beatrix (1871-1872).
* Leigh Behnke â a 20th-century realist, she has made use of the predella format in numerous works (c. 1981â2019)

